UPDATE [dbo].[people]
    SET biography = N'Laura Swift is a British stunt performer and actress. She joined the British Stunt Register in 2016 and holds a Level 3 Health & Safety certification. Her skill set includes firearms handling, kickboxing, wrestling, precision driving, high falls, fire burns, wire work, and motion capture. In addition to her stunt work, Swift is drama school trained and has experience in professional acting roles.

Swift has performed stunts in major films, including Mission: Impossible – Dead Reckoning Part One, Indiana Jones and the Dial of Destiny, Black Widow, and The Batman. She has also worked on television series, including The Sandman Season 2 and The Lazarus Project Season 2. Her stunt doubling credits feature prominent actresses like Cate Blanchett in Disclaimer, Gal Gadot in Disneynulls Snow White, Amber Heard in Aquaman and the Lost Kingdom, and Emma DnullArcy in House of the Dragon Season 2.

In addition to her stunt career, Swift has taken on acting roles, notably starring as Frances in the sci-fi horror film The Rizen (2017). She began her career in acting before transitioning into stunt work, leveraging her physical abilities to expand her opportunities in the entertainment industry.

Swiftnulls filmography also includes appearances in Fast & Furious Presents: Hobbs & Shaw (2019), The Kingnulls Man (2021), and Spooks: The Greater Good (2015).', dob = null, photo_url = 'https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/eMYeKkEYIQ2MCdw4puoHWo65xnn.jpg'
