UPDATE [dbo].[people]
    SET biography = N'Josh Gold is a sound designer and supervising sound editor at Skywalker Sound. He has been a key contributor to several high-profile projects, including How to Train Your Dragon (2010), Rio (2011), TRON: Legacy (2010), The Last Airbender (2010), and Ice Age: Dawn of the Dinosaurs (2009).

Goldnulls talent and dedication have earned him recognition from his peers. Notably, he received a Golden Reel Award in 2011 for his outstanding work on How to Train Your Dragon, specifically in the category of Best Sound Editing for an Animated Feature Film.

In addition to his film work, Gold has contributed to several Marvel Cinematic Universe films, including Iron Man 3 (2013), Thor: The Dark World (2013), Captain America: The Winter Soldier (2014), Ant-Man (2015), Captain America: Civil War (2016), Doctor Strange (2016), Avengers: Infinity War (2018), Avengers: Endgame (2019), Black Widow (2021), and Eternals (2021).

Goldnulls expertise extends to other projects such as Mank (2020), Avatar: The Way of Water (2022), Indiana Jones and the Dial of Destiny (2023), Glass Onion (2022) and The Fantastic Four: First Steps (2025).

His contributions to the sound industry have been recognised with nominations for the prestigious Golden Reel Awards, highlighting his consistent excellence in sound editing.', dob = null, photo_url = 'https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/h2DkaxXLo6K7EGZ8ouuktxSzR7G.jpg'
    WHERE id = 2858;
UPDATE [dbo].[people]
    SET biography = N'Lora Hirschberg (born 1963) is an American sound engineer. She won the Academy Award for Best Sound Mixing for the film Inception and was nominated for the same award for The Dark Knight. She has worked on more than 110 films since 1990.

Description above from the Wikipedia article Lora Hirschberg, licensed under CC-BY-SA, full list of contributors on Wikipedia.', dob = null, photo_url = 'https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/8IJl1itNV99LhKg24yeIGHjYaQd.jpg'
    WHERE id = 2859;
UPDATE [dbo].[people]
    SET biography = N'Dave Jordan started out in the music industry as a record label employee but quickly made the switch to become one of Hollywoodnulls most in-demand theatrical music supervisors. Among the most popular movie series in the world under his guidance are Transformers, Iron Man, Guardians of the Galaxy, Avengers, and Black Panther. Due to his achievements, Dave is now the top-grossing music supervisor in movie history.', dob = null, photo_url = 'https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/btzUgkKCllxClxIgLhmhZ1qaPw.jpg'
    WHERE id = 2860;
UPDATE [dbo].[people]
    SET biography = N'Danielle Dupre is a re-recording mixer based at Skywalker Sound, a division of Lucasfilm. A graduate of the University of Southern Californianulls Thornton School of Music, she initially pursued a career in recording engineering, working with artists such as Prince, DnullAngelo, Mariah Carey, and Justin Bieber at Henson Recording Studios in Los Angeles. In 2012, Dupre transitioned to post-production sound mixing and joined Skywalker Sound, where she has since contributed to over 80 feature films and 20 television series.

Her extensive filmography includes major productions like WandaVision, Obi-Wan Kenobi, 3 Body Problem, Top Gun: Maverick, Wendell & Wild, and Pieces of a Woman. Duprenulls work spans a diverse range of genres, from blockbuster franchises such as Marvel and Star Wars to acclaimed documentaries and independent films.

Throughout her career, Dupre has earned significant recognition for her contributions to sound mixing. She has received four nominations from the Television Academy, including Outstanding Sound Mixing for a Comedy or Drama Series (One Hour) for 3 Body Problem in 2024, Outstanding Sound Mixing for a Limited or Anthology Series or Movie for Obi-Wan Kenobi in 2023, and Outstanding Sound Mixing for a Limited or Anthology Series or Movie for WandaVision in 2021. Additionally, she was nominated for Outstanding Sound Mixing for a Nonfiction or Reality Program for Laurel Canyon: A Place in Time in 2020.', dob = null, photo_url = 'https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/sQBwFVHY40P1KngSw1HS3EVrSWQ.jpg'
    WHERE id = 2861;
UPDATE [dbo].[people]
    SET biography = N'Phil Leonhardt joined Wētā FX in 2005 as a Senior Compositor on Peter Jackson’s King Kong. His expertise quickly became evident, leading to his involvement in many high-profile projects, including X-Men: The Last Stand, Fantastic Four: Rise of the Silver Surfer, The Water Horse, The Day the Earth Stood Still, and The Lovely Bones. He also contributed as a Lighting TD on James Cameron’s groundbreaking Avatar.

Phil’s transition into supervisory roles began with Ridley Scott’s Prometheus, where he oversaw CG and VFX teams. He led major sequences for Man of Steel, The Wolverine, and Furious 7. He supervised the VES Award-nominated Prison Camp sequence in War for the Planet of the Apes and worked on Dawn of the Planet of the Apes.

He led the Iron City team on Alita: Battle Angel before joining the VFX Supervisor team on Marvel’s Avengers: Endgame. Also, Phil was one of Wētā FX’s Visual Effects Supervisors on Kingdom of the Planet of the Apes, earning an HPA Award for his work. He has also received HPA nominations for Maze Runner: The Death Cure and Man of Steel.

In addition to his film work, Phil has played a key role in Wētā FX’s Research and development initiatives. He has led teams developing advanced paint, roto, and compositing tools and contributed to the design of FX libraries, lighting tools for the Physlight pipeline, and deep compositing workflows—particularly in volumetric rendering.

Before working at Wētā FX, Phil built his career in London at Cinesite on the first three Harry Potter films, at MPC on Tomb Raider II and Troy, and at DNEG on The Chronicles of Riddick.', dob = null, photo_url = 'https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/qVnvyg5WA0ZvcUlES8L7E3glnVW.jpg'
    WHERE id = 2862;
UPDATE [dbo].[people]
    SET biography = N'Paul Story is a Senior Animation Supervisor at Wētā FX. Story has been with Wētā FX since 1996, beginning his journey on Peter Jackson’s The Frighteners. Starting out as a Rotoscope Artist, Paul was inspired by the animation team’s work on the film’s ‘Reaper’ character, sparking his ambition to become an animator.

He spent four years in Wētā FX’s creatures department, contributing to developing skeletal and muscle systems for iconic characters such as Gollum and the Cave Troll in The Lord of the Rings trilogy. His dedication and skill eventually led him into animation, where he began animating Gollum, Fellbeasts, and Trolls in The Two Towers. From there, he advanced to leading key sequences in The Return of the King and King Kong.

As an Animation Supervisor, Paul has played a pivotal role in a number of critically acclaimed projects, including The Adventures of Tintin: The Secret of the Unicorn, Iron Man 3, the Planet of the Apes trilogy, and Jon Favreau’s The Jungle Book. His work on Avengers: Infinity War earned him a Visual Effects Society Award for Outstanding Animated Character in a Photoreal Feature for his contributions to Thanos.', dob = null, photo_url = 'https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/DEsoDClRN2TtT0YEpVierpVF6e.jpg'
    WHERE id = 2863;
UPDATE [dbo].[people]
    SET biography = N'Christopher Elke is a visual effects producer at Digital Domain.', dob = null, photo_url = null
    WHERE id = 2864;
UPDATE [dbo].[people]
    SET biography = N'Charlie Endean is a British film and television first assistant director. He earned a First-Class Bachelor of Arts degree in Film, Cinema, and Video Studies from the University of the Arts London in 2005.

Early in his career, Endean built a strong foundation in television, contributing as first assistant director to series like The Midnight Beast (2012), Tatau (2015), Humans (2015), The Last Kingdom (2015), and Vikings (2017-2019). His work on Game of Thrones during seasons 6 and 7, particularly on the pivotal episodes "Battle of the Bastards," "The Winds of Winter," "Spoils of War," and "Eastwatch," earned praise for his ability to coordinate large-scale action, intricate set pieces, and complex logistics. In interviews, he described his role as the nexus between a directornulls vision and production constraints, responsible for script breakdowns, scheduling, and aligning departments such as set design, stunts, digital effects, and extras—a role he likened to keeping "the machine moving fast" while preserving creative integrity.

In film, Endean has worked as first assistant director on major theatrical features including Sergio (2020), The Lost City (2022), and Jurassic World: Dominion (2022), where he also served in an associate producer capacity on the latter two.', dob = null, photo_url = null
    WHERE id = 2865;
UPDATE [dbo].[people]
