    WHERE id = 2866;
UPDATE [dbo].[people]
    SET biography = N'Aaron Cowan is a visual effects producer at Wētā FX, with a career spanning over thirty years in film and television. He began his journey in visual effects working as a VFX coordinator on The Lord of the Rings trilogy. Over time, he took on roles across production, including studio-side VFX production management on films such as The Chronicles of Narnia: The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe and The Waterhorse. Before joining Wētā FX in 2009, he had also worked client-side and on-set in production roles.

At Wētā FX, Cowan started as a sequence manager on Avatar (2009) and advanced through positions such as production manager on The Adventures of Tintin (2011) and digital producer on Dawn of the Planet of the Apes (2014). As a VFX producer, he has overseen major projects including The Last of Us (2023) and Transformers: Rise of the Beasts (2023), as well as Moon Knight (2022). His work on The Last of Us involved creatures, environments, and set extensions across the season, contributing to Wētā’s visual effects output in that television series. In Transformers: Rise of the Beasts, Cowan was credited as VFX producer, working on the creation of hundreds of shots involving Transformers and the Maximals’ home world.

Cowan’s commitments include fostering efficient collaboration between VFX vendors and production teams, aiming for creative and logistical alignment in high-complexity projects. His contributions have earned him nominations from the Hollywood Professional Association. In 2023, he was nominated for the HPA Award for Outstanding Visual Effects – Theatrical Feature for Transformers: Rise of the Beasts, shared with Matt Aitken, Mike Perry, Kevin Estey, and Jong Jin Choi. In the same year, he was also nominated for Outstanding Visual Effects – Episode or Series Season for The Last of Us (Season One), sharing the credit with Simon Jung, David Hampton, Dennis Yoo, and Ben Roberts.', dob = null, photo_url = null
    WHERE id = 2867;
UPDATE [dbo].[people]
    SET biography = N'Daniele Bigi is a visual effects supervisor at Industrial Light & Magic. He joined Industrial Light & Magic’s London studio in January 2015 as CG Supervisor on Marvel’s Ant-Man. His credits as CG Supervisor also include Guardians of the Galaxy and Doctor Strange, both at ILM. Daniele later served as Associate Visual Effects Supervisor on Steven Spielberg’s Ready Player One, for which he received a Visual Effects Society Award for Outstanding Virtual Cinematography in a Photoreal Project. He has since overseen the visual effects for Marvel’s Eternals and contributed to major titles such as Disney’s Aladdin and Lucasfilm’s Star Wars: The Rise of Skywalker.

Originally from Lake Como, Italy, Daniele studied Industrial Design in Milan, where he began exploring 3D computer graphics as a tool for automotive design. A lifelong film enthusiast, he discovered a passion for visual effects as a way to merge his artistic sensibility with his technical skills. This led him to pursue a career in the VFX industry, beginning with smaller studios in Italy before moving on to Aardman Animations, where he joined the emerging 3D department. He then held roles at Framestore and MPC.', dob = null, photo_url = 'https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/r5grrWLtYwA0gozoCRsS9WjCcNk.jpg'
    WHERE id = 2868;
UPDATE [dbo].[people]
    SET biography = N'Kiel Figgins is an Animation Supervisor based in London, working with Industrial Light & Magic (ILM). Originally from the United States and now holding dual U.S.–U.K. citizenship, he began his career in the gaming industry, gaining technical proficiency that later enriched his approach to animation and visual effects.

After entering the professional animation world, Figgins contributed to a variety of projects across major visual-effects studios. His early work includes serving in character animation roles at Digital Domain in Los Angeles, where he worked on notable films such as X-Men: First Class (2011), Oblivion (2013), Into the Storm (2013), and Maleficent (2014).

He then transitioned to freelance roles in London, animating for Double Negative on high-profile features like Avengers: Age of Ultron (2015), Terminator: Genisys (2015), Miss Peregrinenulls Home for Peculiar Children (2016), and Geostorm (2017). Soon after, he joined Framestore as a senior animator, working on Doctor Strange (2016) and King Arthur: Legend of the Sword (2017).

Since joining ILM in London in the fall of 2016, Figgins has steadily taken on leadership roles. He served as senior animator on Ready Player One (2018), moved into lead animator roles for Aladdin (2019), Spider-Man: Far From Home (2019), Star Wars: Rise of Skywalker (2019), Eternals (2021), Jurassic World: Dominion (2022), and as supervisor on Avatar: The Way of Water (2022).

In addition to his feature work, Figgins has engaged in the production of immersive and other media projects at ILM, including ABBA Voyage (2022).

Beyond his studio film work, Figgins has remained active in education and mentorship. He has offered one-on-one animation mentoring through Vertex School since 2021, covering topics ranging from foundational animation principles to production workflow and demo reel development. His academic background includes graduating as Valedictorian with an Associate of Science in Computer Animation from Full Sail Real World Education in 2004, as well as earlier studies in fine art, art history, and new media at the University of Maine and a short figure-drawing course at the Academy of Art College in San Francisco.', dob = null, photo_url = 'https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/uVrLtkVD1CBFgLoAgg8FfchX57Y.jpg'
    WHERE id = 2869;
UPDATE [dbo].[people]
    SET biography = N'Sebastian Lauer is a Visual Effects Supervisor at Rise.', dob = null, photo_url = null
    WHERE id = 2870;
UPDATE [dbo].[people]
    SET biography = N'Mac Smith is a Sound Effects Editor at Skywalker Sound.

A native of Omaha, Nebraska, Smith studied film at the University of Iowa and USC, blending his lifelong passions for music and cinema. His musical abilities led him on tour across the U.S. before he shifted focus to sound editing.  Over the course of his career, he has contributed to more than 100 films and earned 16 Golden Reel Award nominations. In 2022, he received a Primetime Emmy® Award for Outstanding Sound Editing for his work on Marvel’s Moon Knight. Smith has collaborated with acclaimed directors including Robert Zemeckis, Gore Verbinski, and Guillermo del Toro. His diverse filmography features titles such as Up, Enchanted, Tron: Legacy, Dawn of the Planet of the Apes, and Nine Days.

In addition to his work in sound, he is an award-winning documentary producer and director. Smith has been a key member of Skywalker Sound since August 2000.', dob = null, photo_url = 'https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/p9Edy4C8jC1L9Tj9qSm4DqeigD7.jpg'
    WHERE id = 2871;
