UPDATE [dbo].[people]
    SET biography = N'Juan Peralta is a sound re-recording mixer based at Skywalker Sound. He studied at Full Sail Universitynulls Recording Arts program, graduating in or around 1996. After relocating to Los Angeles, he began as a sound technician at post-production house EFX and soon after joined Skywalker Sound — initially working as assistant to sound designer and re-recording mixer Gary Rydstrom, who had worked on Jurassic Park (1993).

Over the years, Peraltanulls responsibilities evolved to those of a full re-recording mixer, and his credits span multiple major motion pictures and video game projects. Among his notable credits are Doctor Strange (2016) and Avengers: Infinity War (2018). He is credited with over 30 films as a re-recording mixer and more than 100 film, TV, and video game credits, including his early mix technician work.

He was part of the sound mixing team for Spider-Man: Across the Spider-Verse (2023), which won the Cinema Audio Society Award for Outstanding Achievement in Sound Mixing for Motion Pictures – Animated in 2024.', dob = null, photo_url = null
