UPDATE [dbo].[people]
    SET biography = N'Riza Aziz brings a background in banking and financial advisory services to the entertainment industry as Chairman and CEO of Red Granite Pictures. With a B.S. in Government and Economics and a masternulls degree in Politics from the London School of Economics, Aziz took on the world of investment banking before venturing off as a mergers and acquisitions advisor for a global clientele. He then turned a talented eye toward the film industry and has been thriving since.

Aziz caught the attention of Hollywood when he was named in Varietynulls "Top Ten Producers to Watch" list in 2011. Aziz has since become the driving force behind the production of films such as Martin Scorsesenulls Academy Award-nominated The Wolf of Wall Street, Jennifer Westfeldtnulls Friends With Kids, Scott Coopernulls Out of the Furnace and Alexandre Ajanulls Horns. Most recently, Red Granite Pictures produced Bobby and Peter Farrellynulls Dumb and Dumber To; released on November 14, 2014. It opened number one at the box office.

Currently, Paramount Pictures and Aziznulls production company Red Granite Pictures in association with Gary Sanchez Productions are working on the Will Ferrell and Mark Wahlberg comedy Daddynulls Home. Red Granite Pictures will co-produce and co-finance the film, which Paramount Pictures will distribute worldwide.

