UPDATE [dbo].[people]
    SET biography = N'Robert Alonzo is a Filipino-American stunt coordinator, fight choreographer, and second-unit director.

Born in Manila, Philippines, and raised in the United States, Alonzo developed an early passion for martial arts and filmmaking, leading to a dynamic and multifaceted career. He trained under Grandmaster Jun Chong and holds black belts in Tae Kwon Do and Hapkido. Academically, he earned a degree in Studio Arts and Communication Studies from Loyola Marymount University, with additional minors in Animation and Business Marketing.

Over nearly three decades, Alonzo has built a résumé of more than 200 credits across film, television, commercials, and music videos. His expertise has made him a trusted collaborator for stars such as Tom Cruise, Dwayne Johnson, Mark Wahlberg, Jeremy Renner, and Jake Gyllenhaal. His second-unit directing credits include major studio productions like Oblivion, Tomorrowland, Deadpool, Bright, Alpha, and The Batman.', dob = '1970-08-04', photo_url = 'https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/7OoQpZ0wdwo8G2zrzNiHhbdfalW.jpg'
    WHERE id = 5742;
UPDATE [dbo].[people]
    SET biography = N'Matthew Sharp is an English key second assistant director. His career spans several decades, during which he has contributed to numerous high-profile films and television series. Sharpnulls expertise has encompassed various roles, including second assistant director, assistant director, unit manager, and set runner, showcasing his versatility and dedication to the craft. He is widely recognised for his pivotal role as the key second assistant director on Star Wars: Episode VIII – The Last Jedi (2017). In addition to his behind-the-scenes contributions, Sharp made a brief on-screen appearance in the same film, portraying Resistance Trench Sergeant nullSalty.null

Throughout his career, Sharp has collaborated on a diverse array of films across various genres. His notable credits include Guardians of the Galaxy (2014), Avengers: Age of Ultron (2015), Doctor Strange in the Multiverse of Madness (2022), and No Time to Die (2021). Sharpnulls work on the Harry Potter series further exemplifies his expertise, with contributions to Harry Potter and the Half-Blood Prince (2009), Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows: Part 1 (2010), and Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows: Part 2 (2011).

Beyond his film work, Sharp has also been involved in television productions, including Pie in the Sky (1995–1997) and The Young Americans (1993).', dob = null, photo_url = 'https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/eUWNR1DY9vqBWLq7vOGaT46FBVx.jpg'
    WHERE id = 5743;
UPDATE [dbo].[people]
    SET biography = N'Bobby Holland Hanton is a stunt performer.

Born in Portsmouth, England, Hanton and a gifted gymnast from an early age, Bobby became a GB-level athlete, developing the strength, agility, and precision to form the backbone of his career in stunt performance.

Hanton made his cinematic debut on Quantum of Solace (2008). Since then, he has become one of Hollywoodnulls most sought-after stunt doubles, working alongside stars such as Chris Hemsworth, Christian Bale, Daniel Craig, and Ryan Reynolds. His resume includes iconic franchises like Thor, The Avengers, Batman, and Star Wars.

Hanton has earned deep respect within the industry because of his commitment to authenticity and safety. His dedication was highlighted in a feature on HBOnulls Real Sports with Bryant Gumbel, which offered a compelling look into lifenulls physical and mental demands as a top-tier stunt performer.

Beyond the screen, Hanton is a passionate advocate for the stunt community. As a Battle Cancer charity ambassador and co-founder of Move Forward Gym, which offers cancer recovery training, he channels his platform into meaningful impact. He is also an active collaborator with the Centr fitness app and maintains a strong connection with fans through his widespread social media presence.

In 2022, he published his first childrenulls book, The Adventures of Eddie and Flip Boy, which was praised for its uplifting message and has inspired young readers worldwide.

Hantonulls achievements have earned him numerous accolades, including a Guinness World Record for "Most targets hit with a backflip throw in one hour" (24), achieved at Pinewood Studios in 2009. He also receives eight Screen Actors Guild Awards, two Emmy Awards for Outstanding Stunt Ensemble on Game of Thrones, and two Taurus World Stunt Awards for "Best Fight" and "Hardest Hit" for Extraction.', dob = '1984-06-11', photo_url = 'https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/qoAkLDUn43DhnyKv5uf0UGXJzpz.jpg'
