    SET biography = N'Liam Neeson (born 7 June 1952) is an Irish actor. He was born in Ballymena, County Antrim, Northern Ireland and educated at Saint Patricknulls College, Ballymena Technical College and Queenulls University Belfast. He moved to Dublin after university to further his acting career, joining the renowned Abbey Theatre. In the early 1990s, he moved again to the United States, where the wide acclaim for his performance in Schindlernulls List led to more high-profile work. He is widowed and lives in New York with his two sons.

