    SET biography = N'Stuart Thorp is a stunt coordinator and performer. Based in Auckland, New Zealand, Thorpnulls notable film credits include serving as the stunt coordinator for James Cameronulls "Avatar" (2009) and its sequel "Avatar: The Way of Water" (2022), as well as for "Zero Dark Thirty" (2012), "Evil Dead Rise" (2023), and "Skyscraper" (2018). He has also worked as an assistant stunt coordinator on films like "Jungle Cruise" (2019) and "The Meg" (2018).

